# i18n/en/overview.ftl — FreeSynergy Themes help texts (English)

help-theme-app-title = FreeSynergy Themes

help-theme-app-body =
    FreeSynergy Themes is the visual theme manager for the FreeSynergy platform.
    It controls the appearance of all apps: colors, typography, cursor, and
    window chrome. Theme changes take effect in real time for all open apps.

    Themes are installed from the Store just like any other package. The official
    catalog includes three themes; more can be found in community repositories.

    Every user can choose their own theme independently. The node administrator
    sets the default theme, but users can override it from this app.

help-theme-app-builtin-title = Built-in Themes

help-theme-app-builtin-body =
    Three themes ship with FreeSynergy by default:

    Midnight Blue (default):
    Dark background with cyan and white accents. Designed for extended use in
    low-light environments. High contrast between primary and accent colors.

    Nordic Dark:
    Muted dark theme inspired by Nordic color palettes. Cooler tone with
    desaturated accents. Easy on the eyes for long sessions.

    Cloud White:
    Light theme with a clean, minimal look. Suitable for bright environments
    and users who prefer light interfaces.

help-theme-app-custom-title = Creating Custom Themes

help-theme-app-custom-body =
    Start from any installed theme and adjust individual CSS variables:
    - --fs-color-primary: main background color
    - --fs-color-accent: highlight and interactive element color
    - --fs-color-text: default text color
    - --fs-font-family: font stack
    - --fs-font-size-base: base font size (default 14px)
    - --fs-radius: border radius for cards and buttons

    Custom themes can be exported as a Store-compatible theme package and
    published to a community repository for others to install.
